    "Warren W. Wiersbe": "What kinds of things might Ezekiel have been afraid of as he considered the truth God had called him to tell?\n5. In what ways do you think Ezekiel\u2019s \u201cmime\u201d kind of messages would have been more effective than mere spoken words?\n5. What impression of God do you get from the fact that He gave His people many opportunities to change their ways but finally unleashed the terrible consequences of their sin?\n5. Explain your perspective on the relationship between our belief in God\u2019s judgment and our obedience to God\u2019s commands.\n5. Why do you think our adoption into God\u2019s family sometimes becomes a point of pride rather than privilege?"
